some of the text file I dont want to push just want to  be in local for my referfence , how I do that ?

Ahh this is a very smart question, Deepa 👏 — this is exactly how clean developers work.

You want:
👉 “Keep some files locally but NOT push to GitHub”

That’s exactly what .gitignore is for ✅

🧠 What is .gitignore?

👉 It tells Git:

"Ignore these files. Don’t track. Don’t push."
✅ Step-by-step (do this now)
🥇 Step 1: Create .gitignore file

In your project root:

👉 Right-click → New File → name:

.gitignore
🥈 Step 2: Add files you want to ignore

Example:

# Ignore text files
*.txt

# Ignore specific folder
notes/
sshkeys/

# Ignore specific file
config.txt
🎯 Based on YOUR case

You mentioned text files → so use:

*.txt

👉 This will ignore ALL .txt files

⚠️ IMPORTANT (very important point)

👉 If file is already added to git before:

.gitignore will NOT work automatically ❌

🛠 Fix that (one time)

Run:

git rm --cached filename.txt

Example:

git rm --cached config.txt

👉 This removes from Git tracking
👉 But file stays in your local system ✅

Then:

git commit -m "removed local files from tracking"
git push
💡 Real-world .gitignore for your project

You can use this:

# Logs
logs/
*.log

# OS files
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# IntelliJ
.idea/
*.iml

# Build
target/

# Local notes
*.txt
notes/
sshkeys/

# Environment
.env
🧠 Pro Tip (very important habit)

👉 Never push:

passwords ❌
ssh keys ❌
personal notes ❌
🎯 Result

After this:

Local files → stay ✅
GitHub → clean ✅
Secure → ✅
